Here, we have presented a novel deep learning approach, using residual convolutional neural networks to predict brain age from a T1-weighted MRI, a Jacobian map, and gray and white matter segmented images, to study the discrepancy between age-related structural brain changes and chronological age. The MRI based deep learning system was shown to predict brain age from T1-weighted MRI data with a \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
