The residual block, displayed in Fig. 4, consists of a combination of layers which are repeated twice inside the residual blocks. This combination is composed of a 3D convolutional layer with stride 1 × 1 × 1 and kernel size 3 × 3 × 3, a batch re-normalization layer60, and an ELU activation function61. The defining element of the residual block is the skip connection which adds the signal feeding into the residual block to the output of a layer close to the end of the block. The number of feature maps in block number \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
